===== Frontal lobe

The frontal lobe, situated anterior to the central sulcus, is the largest cortical lobe, associated with high-level cognitive functions. It is composed of three main structures: the #acr("PFC"), the premotor cortex and the motor cortex. The #acr("PFC"), occupying the anterior frontal lobe, is not a single homogeneous structure but a collection of interconnected cortical regions. It can be subdivised along the dorsal-ventral and medial-lateral axes.

- the #acr("dlPFC"), located on the lateral surface of the frontal lobe;
- the #acr("dmPFC"),  located along the medial and d surfaces of the frontal lobe;
- the #acr("vlPFC"), located on the inferior lateral frontal surface;
- the #acr("vmPFC"), located along the medial and ventral surfaces of the frontal lobe;
- the #acr("OFC"), located on the ventral surface of the frontal lobe (above the eye sockets);

